            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_4.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_1_5.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "For gravy, heat 2 tbsp oil, saute onions and green chillies till onions are brown. Add ginger garlic paste, saute for a minute. Then add turmeric, red chilli, coriander and cumin powder and saute for another minute. ",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_3.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_4.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Add cashews, tomatoes and saute for one minute. Keep stirring till the tomatoes starts to leave oil. Once it cools down, make a fine paste.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_3_3.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "In a kadai or pan, heat remaining 1 tbsp oil. Then add cardamom, bay leaves, cinnamon, cloves, shahjeera and allow it to sizzle. Add ground paste prepared before and mix it well with water to a desired consistency.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_2.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_4_3.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Add garam masala, kasuri methi and mix it well. Simmer the gravy on a low flame for 7-8 minutes. Switch off the stove and add cream. Add koftas few minutes before serving to preserve crispiness.",
